The paper deals with the recovery of sparse signals in a specific basis expansion, namely the Wigner-D basis, which is related to spherical harmonics and has applications in antenna measurement. This suggests that the paper could belong to sub-categories related to signal processing (cs.SP), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), computational geometry (cs.CG), and possibly scientific computing (cs.SI).
